              "answers": {
                "answer_3": {
                  "score": 0.0,
                  "response": "Consider This: In the wake of the confusion surrounding the 2000 presidential election, in 2002 Congress passed the Help America Vote Act. This measure was designed to replace the haphazard, stateby-state process that had existed for two centuries. LO 13.1: Describe the legal challenges that have broadened the democratic character of elections in America."
